    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1641"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1641">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/11.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 10, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government informs me that a 5-kilo wireless watt apparatus was ordered about
                    November 14 from Flint &amp; Walling, New York, to be erected on the National
                    Theater, Panama, for Government use. A portion of it has lately been received.
                    Subinspector Clark says such an apparatus will seriously interfere with the
                    proposed Navy apparatus at Balboa and near Culebra. I have therefore obtained
                    from the Minister for Foreign Affairs a delay of installation pending
                    Department’s instruction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
